            "body": "@lewis6991 Why did you close this issue?\n1. The issues mentioned by @andrewbraxton talk about adding new option to clangd. When the option is added this will not solve the issue in nvim automatically, it would still need to use this new option.\n2. As I mentioned the retrovim with ALE plugin is able to behave correctly with the same version of clangd so I do not think it is a clangd dproblem or, at least, the problem can be solved without changes in clangd.\n\nIt also seems to me that the clang issues are about different use case and will probably not solve this problem.\n\nPlease reopen.",
