        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "It seems like there's a collection of slightly different issues with symlinks that clangd has. The issue I frequently run into is go-to-definition bringing me to the declaration in the header file instead of the actual definition in the source file when the source file is inside a symlinked directory as represented in compile_commands.json.\n\nLooking at the LSP's logs, we see clangd is indeed returning the header file as the location of the definition (until I manually open the source file, then clangd will start returning the source file):\n\n```\n[ERROR][2024-12-29 15:06:22] ...p/_transport.lua:36     \"rpc\"   \"clangd\"        \"stderr\"        \"I[15:06:22.150] <-- textDocument/definition(6)\\n\"\n[ERROR][2024-12-29 15:06:22] ...p/_transport.lua:36     \"rpc\"   \"clangd\"        \"stderr\"        \"V[15:06:22.150] ASTWorker running Definitions on version 0 of /Users/brax/projects/sandbox/clangd-symlink/main/main.c\\n\"\n[ERROR][2024-12-29 15:06:22] ...p/_transport.lua:36     \"rpc\"   \"clangd\"        \"stderr\"        \"I[15:06:22.151] --> reply:textDocument/definition(6) 0 ms\\n\"\n[ERROR][2024-12-29 15:06:22] ...p/_transport.lua:36     \"rpc\"   \"clangd\"        \"stderr\"        'V[15:06:22.151] >>> {\"id\":6,\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"result\":[{\"range\":{\"end\":{\"character\":8,\"line\":0},\"start\":{\"character\":5,\"line\":0}},\"uri\":\"file:///Users/brax/projects/sandbox/clangd-symlink/symlink/foo.h\"}]}\\n\\n'\n```\n\nSo at least in my case, there's clearly nothing Neovim can be expected to reasonably do here. It's simply getting the \"wrong answer\" from clangd. I think burden of proof would be on OP to prove that Neovim is doing something wrong in his specific case, because it still sounds like a clangd issue -- Neovim has no control over how clangd indexes the project.",
